<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042391>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Two-chambered gas bladders of Stelliferinae, left & right halves represent different forms or taxa. A. left, Bairdiella, Corvula, Elattarchus, Odontoscion & Stellifer (Ophioscion); right, S. naso & S. venezuelae. B. left, S. microps, hatched area indicates drumming muscle patch; right, small knob-like such as S. griseus, S. colonensis, S. lanceolatus, etc. C. left, S. brasiliensis; right, S. rastrifer." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5042391/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5042431>
    dc:description "FIGURE 18. Detail of nostrils shape for: A- Stellifer menezesi new species; B- Stellifer gomezi. Scale: 10 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5042431/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

